{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-14",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_14_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "La Paloma",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 3,
  "page_total": 5,
  "page_start_sec": 491.88,
  "page_end_sec": 733.72,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.72,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 491.88,
      "end": 493.54,
      "text": "But I got a hunch you ain't going"
    },
    {
      "start": 493.82,
      "end": 494.72,
      "text": "all the way with me."
    },
    {
      "start": 495.15,
      "end": 497.28,
      "text": "What's the honest to God on this guy,"
    },
    {
      "start": 497.38,
      "end": 497.62,
      "text": "Sam?"
    },
    {
      "start": 498.3,
      "end": 499.78,
      "text": "You don't have to kick back on me."
    },
    {
      "start": 500.26,
      "end": 501.34,
      "text": "You know I'm regular."
    },
    {
      "start": 502.592,
      "end": 504.56,
      "text": "Spade lifted his eyes from the silver dome.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 504.8,
      "end": 506.36,
      "text": "They were clear and candid."
    },
    {
      "start": 507.16,
      "end": 507.68,
      "text": "Sure you are,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 507.82,
      "end": 508.34,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 508.56,
      "end": 509.96,
      "text": "I'm not holding out."
    },
    {
      "start": 510.5,
      "end": 511.64,
      "text": "I gave you it straight."
    },
    {
      "start": 512.46,
      "end": 513.62,
      "text": "I'm doing a job for him,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 513.86,
      "end": 515.92,
      "text": "but he's got some friends that look wrong to me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 516.0,
      "end": 517.56,
      "text": "and I'm a little leery of him."
    },
    {
      "start": 518.09,
      "end": 520.62,
      "text": "the kid we chased out yesterday was one of his"
    },
    {
      "start": 520.62,
      "end": 524.26,
      "text": "friends yes luke he was and it was one of them"
    },
    {
      "start": 524.26,
      "end": 527.6,
      "text": "that shoved miles across spade shook his head"
    },
    {
      "start": 527.77,
      "end": 531.88,
      "text": "thursby killed miles and who killed him spade"
    },
    {
      "start": 532.24,
      "end": 535.0,
      "text": "smiled that's supposed to be a secret but"
    },
    {
      "start": 535.04,
      "end": 537.72,
      "text": "confidentially i did he said according to the"
    },
    {
      "start": 537.8,
      "end": 540.5,
      "text": "police luke grunted and stood up saying"
    },
    {
      "start": 540.71,
      "end": 542.58,
      "text": "you're a tough one to figure out sam"
    },
    {
      "start": 543.22,
      "end": 544.24,
      "text": "come on we'll have"
    },
    {
      "start": 544.42,
      "end": 544.98,
      "text": "that look-see."
    },
    {
      "start": 546.02,
      "end": 547.5,
      "text": "They stopped at the desk long enough",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 547.5,
      "end": 549.92,
      "text": "for Luke to fix it so we'll get a ring"
    },
    {
      "start": 549.92,
      "end": 552.48,
      "text": "if he comes in and went up to Cairo's room."
    },
    {
      "start": 553.44,
      "end": 554.86,
      "text": "Cairo's bed was smooth and trim,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 555.02,
      "end": 555.96,
      "text": "but paper in"
    },
    {
      "start": 555.96,
      "end": 556.68,
      "text": "the wastebasket,"
    },
    {
      "start": 556.84,
      "end": 558.58,
      "text": "unevenly drawn blinds,"
    },
    {
      "start": 558.58,
      "end": 561.08,
      "text": "and a couple of rumpled towels in the bathroom showed"
    },
    {
      "start": 561.36,
      "end": 564.28,
      "text": "that the chambermaid had not yet been in that morning."
    },
    {
      "start": 565.344,
      "end": 567.12,
      "text": "Cairo's luggage consisted of a square",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 567.22,
      "end": 567.56,
      "text": "trunk,"
    },
    {
      "start": 567.66,
      "end": 568.5,
      "text": "a valise,"
    },
    {
      "start": 568.74,
      "end": 569.96,
      "text": "and a gladstone bag."
    },
    {
      "start": 571.0,
      "end": 573.08,
      "text": "His bathroom cabinet was stocked with cosmetics,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 573.46,
      "end": 573.88,
      "text": "boxes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 574.52,
      "end": 574.66,
      "text": "cans,"
    },
    {
      "start": 575.14,
      "end": 575.5,
      "text": "jars,"
    },
    {
      "start": 575.7,
      "end": 576.98,
      "text": "and bottles of powders,"
    },
    {
      "start": 577.04,
      "end": 577.54,
      "text": "creams,"
    },
    {
      "start": 577.92,
      "end": 578.72,
      "text": "unguents,"
    },
    {
      "start": 578.88,
      "end": 579.6,
      "text": "perfumes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 579.6,
      "end": 580.1,
      "text": "lotions,"
    },
    {
      "start": 580.12,
      "end": 580.78,
      "text": "and tonics."
    },
    {
      "start": 581.6,
      "end": 583.64,
      "text": "Two suits and an overcoat hung in the closet",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 583.64,
      "end": 585.84,
      "text": "over three pairs of carefully treed shoes."
    },
    {
      "start": 586.9,
      "end": 588.94,
      "text": "The valise and smaller bag were unlocked.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 589.88,
      "end": 592.12,
      "text": "Luke had the trunk unlocked by the time Spade had",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 592.22,
      "end": 593.16,
      "text": "finished searching elsewhere."
    },
    {
      "start": 594.336,
      "end": 594.92,
      "text": "Blank so far,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 595.14,
      "end": 595.72,
      "text": "Spade said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 595.9,
      "end": 597.76,
      "text": "as they dug down into the trunk."
    },
    {
      "start": 598.46,
      "end": 600.26,
      "text": "They found nothing there to interest them."
    },
    {
      "start": 601.14,
      "end": 603.38,
      "text": "Any particular thing we're supposed to be looking for?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 603.62,
      "end": 605.64,
      "text": "Luke asked as he locked the trunk again."
    },
    {
      "start": 606.06,
      "end": 607.04,
      "text": "No,"
    },
    {
      "start": 607.88,
      "end": 609.79,
      "text": "he's supposed to have come here from Constantinople.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 610.88,
      "end": 611.88,
      "text": "I'd like to know if he did.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 612.08,
      "end": 614.68,
      "text": "I haven't seen anything that says he didn't."
    },
    {
      "start": 615.584,
      "end": 616.24,
      "text": "What's his racket?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 617.248,
      "end": 618.14,
      "text": "Spade shook his head.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 618.43,
      "end": 620.26,
      "text": "That's something else I'd like to know."
    },
    {
      "start": 621.24,
      "end": 623.44,
      "text": "He crossed the room and bent down over the wastebasket.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 623.7,
      "end": 624.24,
      "text": "Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 624.74,
      "end": 625.9,
      "text": "this is our last shot."
    },
    {
      "start": 626.56,
      "end": 628.4,
      "text": "He took a newspaper from the basket."
    },
    {
      "start": 628.58,
      "end": 631.86,
      "text": "His eyes brightened when he saw it was the previous day's"
    },
    {
      "start": 632.0,
      "end": 632.14,
      "text": "call."
    },
    {
      "start": 632.9,
      "end": 636.1,
      "text": "It was folded with a classified advertising page outside.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 636.88,
      "end": 637.54,
      "text": "He opened it,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 637.6,
      "end": 638.94,
      "text": "examined that page,"
    },
    {
      "start": 639.04,
      "end": 640.66,
      "text": "and nothing there stopped his eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 641.36,
      "end": 643.66,
      "text": "He turned the paper over and looked at the page that had"
    },
    {
      "start": 643.66,
      "end": 644.54,
      "text": "been folded inside,"
    },
    {
      "start": 645.42,
      "end": 647.58,
      "text": "the page that held financial and shipping news,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 648.06,
      "end": 648.48,
      "text": "the weather,"
    },
    {
      "start": 648.64,
      "end": 649.24,
      "text": "births,"
    },
    {
      "start": 649.24,
      "end": 649.78,
      "text": "marriages,"
    },
    {
      "start": 650.16,
      "end": 650.54,
      "text": "divorces,"
    },
    {
      "start": 650.56,
      "end": 651.04,
      "text": "and deaths."
    },
    {
      "start": 651.39,
      "end": 653.28,
      "text": "From the lower left-hand corner,"
    },
    {
      "start": 653.44,
      "end": 655.18,
      "text": "a little more than two inches of the"
    },
    {
      "start": 655.26,
      "end": 657.58,
      "text": "bottom of the second column had been torn out."
    },
    {
      "start": 658.656,
      "end": 660.68,
      "text": "Immediately above the tear was a small caption.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 660.94,
      "end": 662.36,
      "text": "arrived today,"
    },
    {
      "start": 662.66,
      "end": 665.9,
      "text": "followed by 12.20 a.m."
    },
    {
      "start": 665.94,
      "end": 667.54,
      "text": "Capek from Astoria,"
    },
    {
      "start": 667.76,
      "end": 669.78,
      "text": "5.05 a.m."
    },
    {
      "start": 669.82,
      "end": 670.72,
      "text": "Helen P."
    },
    {
      "start": 670.86,
      "end": 671.92,
      "text": "Drew from Greenwood,"
    },
    {
      "start": 672.7,
      "end": 674.04,
      "text": "5.06 a.m.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 674.656,
      "end": 676.04,
      "text": "Alborado from Bandon."
    },
    {
      "start": 676.56,
      "end": 678.52,
      "text": "The terror passed through the next line,"
    },
    {
      "start": 678.62,
      "end": 679.8,
      "text": "leaving only enough of its"
    },
    {
      "start": 679.88,
      "end": 682.48,
      "text": "letters to make from Sydney inferable."
    },
    {
      "start": 683.456,
      "end": 685.9,
      "text": "Spade put the call down on the desk and looked into the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 686.16,
      "end": 686.74,
      "text": "wastebasket again."
    },
    {
      "start": 687.33,
      "end": 689.46,
      "text": "He found a small piece of wrapping paper,"
    },
    {
      "start": 689.68,
      "end": 690.8,
      "text": "a piece of string,"
    },
    {
      "start": 691.1,
      "end": 692.14,
      "text": "two hosiery"
    },
    {
      "start": 692.32,
      "end": 692.44,
      "text": "tags,"
    },
    {
      "start": 693.24,
      "end": 696.3,
      "text": "a haberdasher's sale ticket for half a dozen pairs of socks,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 696.58,
      "end": 697.1,
      "text": "and,"
    },
    {
      "start": 697.2,
      "end": 698.76,
      "text": "in the bottom of the basket,"
    },
    {
      "start": 698.98,
      "end": 701.62,
      "text": "a piece of newspaper rolled into a tiny ball."
    },
    {
      "start": 702.74,
      "end": 703.9,
      "text": "He opened the ball carefully,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 704.12,
      "end": 704.92,
      "text": "smoothed it out"
    },
    {
      "start": 704.92,
      "end": 705.53,
      "text": "on the desk,"
    },
    {
      "start": 705.64,
      "end": 707.76,
      "text": "and fitted it into the torn part of the call."
    },
    {
      "start": 708.7,
      "end": 710.24,
      "text": "The fit at the sides was exact,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 710.8,
      "end": 712.18,
      "text": "but between the top of the crumpled"
    },
    {
      "start": 712.18,
      "end": 714.78,
      "text": "fragment and the inferable from Sidney half,"
    },
    {
      "start": 714.98,
      "end": 715.72,
      "text": "an inch was"
    },
    {
      "start": 715.86,
      "end": 716.18,
      "text": "missing,"
    },
    {
      "start": 716.26,
      "end": 718.72,
      "text": "sufficient space to have held announcement"
    },
    {
      "start": 718.72,
      "end": 720.32,
      "text": "of six or seven boats' arrival."
    },
    {
      "start": 721.46,
      "end": 721.9,
      "text": "He turned the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 721.9,
      "end": 724.08,
      "text": "sheet over and saw that the other side of the"
    },
    {
      "start": 724.08,
      "end": 726.92,
      "text": "missing portion could have held only a meaningless"
    },
    {
      "start": 727.12,
      "end": 729.28,
      "text": "corner of a stockbroker's advertisement."
    },
    {
      "start": 730.28,
      "end": 730.48,
      "text": "Luke,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 730.68,
      "end": 731.86,
      "text": "leaning over his shoulder,"
    },
    {
      "start": 732.02,
      "end": 732.34,
      "text": "asked,"
    },
    {
      "start": 732.94,
      "end": 733.72,
      "text": "What's this all about?"
    }
  ]
}